  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (environmental-factors gap)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). NOTE: validation activities were conducted exclusively under controlled laboratory conditions (22 °C, 1 atm, no EM interference); the operating envelope for deployed CPB suites — which experience temperature drift (18–26 °C), variable ambient pressure in transport/altitude contexts, and significant electromagnetic interference from adjacent perfusion equipment — is not characterised in any validation result or sensitivity study linked to this package.",
