      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-vr-flow-bench-22c",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Flow-bench hemolysis validation at 22 °C, atmospheric pressure",
      "description": "Blood-analogue fluid (glycerol-water) circulated through the FDA generic centrifugal pump test rig. Five flow-speed operating points measured. All tests conducted in a climate-controlled laboratory at 22 ± 0.5 °C and 101.3 kPa. Relative hemolysis index (RHI) computed from CFD matched measured values within 8 % at all five operating points. No thermal sensitivity sweep performed; humidity and EMI conditions not recorded or controlled. No environmental-sensitivity study is linked to these results."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-vr-mesh-convergence",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh-convergence and discretisation error study",
      "description": "Grid-convergence index (GCI) computed across three mesh refinement levels (4.2 M, 11.6 M, 28.4 M hexahedral cells). GCI < 2 % for all quantities of interest at the medium refinement level selected for production runs. Study performed under identical isothermal laboratory conditions as the flow-bench validation; no variation in ambient temperature or pressure was introduced."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-vr-solver-verification",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Numerical solver verification against analytical benchmark",
      "description": "ANSYS Fluent 2023R1 verified against the Taylor–Green vortex benchmark and a rotating-disk Couette flow with analytical solution. Residual norms converged to 1 × 10⁻⁶. Verification conducted on isolated compute node; no EMI characterisation performed. Temperature of compute hardware monitored for numerical stability only; fluid-domain thermal effects on blood viscosity at elevated operating-room temperatures not assessed."
    }
  ],
