      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions documented with sufficient detail to reproduce the experimental configuration; fluid properties and boundary conditions recorded.",
      "rationale": "Laboratory test conditions documented: 22 ± 0.5 °C, 101.3 kPa, glycerol-water blood analogue at 3.5 cP viscosity, five flow-speed combinations (2–6 L/min, 2000–4000 RPM). Temperature was the sole environmental parameter recorded. Humidity, electromagnetic interference levels, and altitude-related pressure variation were not characterised. This single-temperature snapshot satisfies the nominal MRL 2 documentation requirement but does not bound the full deployment environmental envelope."
    },
