      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly linked to clinical hemolysis endpoint; scalar hemolysis index accepted as surrogate for plasma-free haemoglobin elevation.",
      "rationale": "RHI is the regulatory-accepted scalar metric for comparative hemolysis assessment per FDA guidance. Direct correspondence to clinical plasma-free haemoglobin established in literature. QoI relevance confirmed for MRL 2 COU."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation geometry, flow regime, and fluid properties sufficiently similar to COU device and operating conditions.",
      "rationale": "FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry used as validation surrogate is geometrically representative of the Class II CPB device class. Flow regime (turbulent, Re 4000–18000) and fluid analogue viscosity match COU operating range. Validation activities are relevant to the COU at the pump-fluid interaction level. However, the validation environment (controlled lab at 22 °C, 1 atm, no EMI) does not replicate the full range of conditions encountered in deployed CPB suites, where ambient temperature may vary from 18–26 °C, altitude-adjusted pressure may differ by ±5 kPa during air transport, and perfusion consoles generate significant electromagnetic fields. No environmental-sensitivity study is referenced to bridge this gap."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 for this factor; scoped out per project credibility plan.",
      "rationale": "Numerical solver error beyond discretisation and code verification is not required at MRL 2 for this COU. Factor scoped out in project credibility plan consistent with ASME V&V 40 Table 5-1 requirements."
    },
