      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; analyst competency documented through institutional training records.",
      "rationale": "Use error assessment not required at MRL 2. Lead analyst holds CFD certification; training records on file. Factor not assessed per credibility plan."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model selection justified with reference to comparable rotating-flow validation studies; hemolysis power-law constants sourced from peer-reviewed literature.",
      "rationale": "SST k-ω turbulence model selected based on demonstrated performance in rotating impeller flows (Giersiepen et al. 1990; Goubergrits & Affeld 2004). Hemolysis power-law constants (C = 1.228 × 10⁻⁷, α = 0.7762, β = 2.416) from Giersiepen et al. Blood viscosity modelled as Newtonian at 3.5 cP, consistent with laboratory analogue fluid. Model form does not account for temperature-dependent viscosity variation across the deployment thermal envelope."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All boundary conditions and material properties documented with uncertainty bounds; inlet flow rate uncertainty ≤ 2 %.",
      "rationale": "Inlet boundary conditions (flow rate ± 0.5 %, rotational speed ± 10 RPM) documented. Fluid density and viscosity specified at 22 °C. Pump wall geometry sourced from FDA benchmark CAD file. Input uncertainty quantification performed for flow rate and rotational speed only. Temperature-dependent viscosity and density variation across the 18–26 °C deployment range not propagated through the model; this constitutes an uncharacterised input uncertainty in the deployed context."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 for Class II device with blood-analogue validation fluid.",
      "rationale": "Test sample characterisation beyond fluid property specification not required at MRL 2. Glycerol-water analogue batch viscosity verified at 22 °C prior to testing. Factor not assessed per credibility plan."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Dimensionless flow and speed parameters (flow coefficient, head coefficient) match between validation experiment and COU operating points within 5 %.",
      "rationale": "Flow coefficient Φ and head coefficient Ψ computed for all five operating points. Validation experiment and COU operating points agree within 3.2 % for Φ and 4.1 % for Ψ. Equivalency established at nominal 22 °C laboratory conditions. No equivalency check performed at the temperature and pressure extremes of the deployment envelope (18–26 °C, 96–106 kPa), where fluid viscosity and density shifts would alter Reynolds number by up to 12 % and potentially shift the operating point on the pump performance curve."
    }
